title: Facebook CEO says delay in flagging fake Pelosi video was 'execution mistake'
text: Facebook Inc Chief Executive Mark Zuckerberg on Wednesday said his social media company took too long to flag as false an altered video of U.S. House Speaker Nancy Pelosi that appeared to show the Democratic Representative slurring and tripping through a speech.

title: What is the Libra Association going to do, really?
text: When Facebook unveiled Libra a few days ago, the company also announced the Libra Association, a not-for-profit that will oversee all things Libra. Facebook wants to make sure that everyone is aware that Libra was created by Facebook but isn’t controlled by Facebook.

title: Instagram's Mosseri On Deepfakes: 'If It Takes Too Long To Identify It...The Damage Is Done'
